article.headline: UC Davis 92, Cal St.-Fullerton 86
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Dominic Calegari scored 28 points and pulled down 10 rebounds to lead UC Davis past Cal State Fullerton 92-86 in overtime on Saturday in the final regular season game for both teams. The win gave UC Davis the No. 4 seed and a bye in the upcoming Big West Conference tournament, which begins next week. Cal State Fullerton grabbed the No. 5 seed and will play Cal State Northridge on Wednesday. The Aggies (13-17, 8-8) were up 75-72 with less than 10 seconds left in regulation when Jacques Streeter sank a 3-pointer for the Titans (15-14, 8-8) to tie it and send the game into overtime. From there, however, the Aggies outscored their opponents 17-11 for the win. Julian Welch finished with 18 points for the Aggies. Streeter and Gerard Anderson each scored 23 points for the Titans. Devon Peltier added 20 points and Jer'Vaughn Johnson finished with 14 points and 11 rebounds.
